      "name": "Hemolysis model adequacy assessment via published literature survey",
      "description": "A structured review of published hemolysis model studies was conducted to assess the adequacy of the power-law hemolysis model for CFD-based pump analysis. Seventeen peer-reviewed sources covering the Giersiepen-Wurzinger and modified hemolysis models were surveyed. The review concluded that the model form is consistent with accepted practice for MRL 2 assessments and that published relative hemolysis index values for comparable centrifugal pumps fall within the expected RH < 1 range. The literature body was judged sufficient to support the validation claim without additional bench testing.",
